HEADWORD: Murine
<hw>Mu"rine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>murinus</ets>, from <ets>mus</ets>, <ets>muris</ets>, mouse: cf. F.
<ets>murin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to a family
of rodents (<fam>Muridae</fam>), of which the mouse is the
type.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Murine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Murine
<hw>Mu"rine</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a tribe
of rodents, of which the mouse is the type.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muringer</ent>⟦br⟧
